[8] Pakistan (Lahore)
Date: Fri 19 Apr 2013
Source: The Frontier Post [edited]
http://www.thefrontierpost.com/article/6625/


Measles has killed 12 children and affected dozens in Lahore in the past one week, the Frontier Post News desk reported. During the last 24 hours, 23 children were admitted in Mayo Hospital and 22 in Children's Hospital; of them 3, hailing from Lahore, succumbed to the fatal disease.

In district Jhang, 10 children have died of measles in the past 3 months, while in Multan, 195 have been affected.

Lahore is badly affected by the disease; however, measles cases have also been reported in other cities of the province.

