[9] Pakistan (Sindh)
Date: Thu 18 Apr 2013
Source: The International Tribune [edited]
http://tribune.com.pk/story/536965/new-chief-secretary-concerned-about-measles-outbreak/


The newly appointed Sindh Chief Secretary (CS), Muhammad Ijaz Chaudhry, has directed the health secretary to submit a report on the measles outbreak in the province. On his 1st day at work, Chaudhry noted that 3000 children were affected by measles, and nearly 120 were killed across Sindh. The new CS has also asked for a report on strikes by the Hyderabad taluka municipal staff from the local government secretary within 2 days. He demanded a comprehensive report with facts and solutions from the relevant departments.

